last_episode_to_air.overview: Winston and Dudley try to get one of Ham's stories published. Unfortunately in their rush, the book they take the publisher turns out to be Ham's super top secret diary. Oops!

name: Winston Steinburger and Sir Dudley Ding Dong
original_name: Winston Steinburger and Sir Dudley Ding Dong
overview: Winston Steinburger and Sir Dudley Ding Dong follows the intergalactic exploits of Winston Steinburger, his cat Dudley, and a high-strung alien named Hampton - three unlikely amigos in the Globulus Galaxy; a busy stretch of alien-infused space, millions of moons from earth.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Winston Steinburger and Sir Dudley Ding Dong follows the intergalactic exploits of Winston Steinburger, his cat Dudley, and a high-strung alien named Hampton - three unlikely amigos in the Globulus Galaxy; a busy stretch of alien-infused space, millions of moons from earth.

episodes.name: Party Pants Bromance
episodes.overview: It's Winston's first 'New Galaxy's Night' in space, and he's super stoked! Just one problem... HE LOST HIS TICKET! And it could be ANYWHERE IN THE GALAXY!

episodes.name: Very Fast Forward
episodes.overview: Winston builds an invention to go back in time and retrieve everything he's ever borrowed from Hampton. He finds all of Ham's stuff, but Ham gets stranded in the past!

episodes.name: Love and Rockets
episodes.overview: Sgt. Sasha Spritz holds a contest: capture a criminal and you can hang out with him! Win tries to capture notorious criminal Bad Nana, but she captures Dudley instead.

episodes.name: Hitchhiker's Guide to Gastronomy
episodes.overview: Winston tries to teleport to speed up his diner deliveries.

episodes.name: Eat My Dust, Space Witch
episodes.overview: Win is pumped to race in the Globulus Grand-Prix, but isn't old enough to enter. Win drinks an aging potion, and soon finds that now he can't stop getting older!

episodes.name: Evil Interns
episodes.overview: Winston is given the opportunity to work on his inventions on The Cosmic Candy Cruise Ship. Things go from sweet to sour when he realises his work is helping to enslave the galaxy!

episodes.name: Camp Coppawannastopya
episodes.overview: Win can't wait to show off his awesome Spacecopping skills at Sgt. Sasha Spritz's Spacecop Camp... until his gangly rival Brad proceeds to outdo Win at everything!

episodes.name: The Greasiest Greasetrap In The Galaxy
episodes.overview: Win and the gang get sucked into Cutty's grease trap, discovering a strange world of aliens who want to use the guys as a peace offering to the monster terrorising their world.

episodes.name: Smashing It
episodes.overview: Winston wants to break a record so he can be in the Globulus Book of Especially Epic Records. But with the stuffy official Viktor Flug in charge, Win just can't catch a break.

episodes.name: Rip Van Wrinkles
episodes.overview: Winston wants a TURBO TUNA, but has no cash. When a hip, old dude named Murray offers to GIVE him a Turbo Tuna in exchange for a favour, things get out of control.

episodes.name: Safety First
episodes.overview: Hampton modifies Winston's hoverplank to try to keep him safe at the Butt Crusher Games. When Ham's tampering gets Win injured, Ham has to take Win's place in the competition.

episodes.name: Prank Day
episodes.overview: It's Pam's legendary Prank Day and Winston is her number one target! After one of her pranks takes it too far for Win, he vows revenge.

episodes.name: The Most Important Meal Of The Day
episodes.overview: Win and co visit the planet where their favourite cereal is made and discover it's been taken over by the Coffee King... and he's replacing the cereal with... coffee! Yuck.

episodes.name: A Beef History Of Time
episodes.overview: Cutty asks Win and Dud to make a burger delivery to The Dark Lord, but their delivery is late. Really late. The Dark Lord isn't impressed and teaches them a lesson in punctuality.

episodes.name: Hampton Family Reunion
episodes.overview: On the eve of Hampton's family reunion, Ham reveals he's been telling his fam that he is the hero of the group. Now Win and Dud have to play along with the charade.

episodes.name: Father Of Invention
episodes.overview: When one of Win's inventions sends Dud to the hospital, he decides that he is done with inventions and adventure forever! A mech attack forces Win to reconsider his decision.

episodes.name: Spritzed
episodes.overview: Sargeant Sasha Spritz loses his moustache and quits being a Spacecop, convinced he's lost his mojo. But without Spritz's crime fighting skills, the galaxy starts to fall into chaos.

episodes.name: Bikers In Space
episodes.overview: Cutty goes on vacation, leaving the Diner in Win's hands. When a bunch of mean bikers arrive and cause chaos, the guys have to get them out and fix up the Diner before Cutty returns.

episodes.name: Day Of The Dud
episodes.overview: Pam kidnaps Dudley, so she can steal his identity using her holo-jammies. Now Pam can finally spend some one-on-one time with Win! What could possibly go wrong?

episodes.name: Map Day
episodes.overview: Win and the gang buy a treasure map from a shady robot, but end up being caught in an elaborate conspiracy masterminded by the Dark Lord!

episodes.name: Finding Num Num
episodes.overview: Winston Steinburger & Sir Dudley Ding Dong is a fast-paced, high-energy animated comedy that follows the intergalactic exploits of Winston Steinburger, his cat Dudley & a high-strung alien named Hampton- three unlikely amigos

episodes.name: Goat Dude 4
episodes.overview: Winston installs a video games arcade in the Diner as a way to bring in more customers. While playing 'Goat Dude 4' he soon realises it's more than just a game.

episodes.name: Opposites Attack
episodes.overview: When Winston invents a helmet that can translate languages, Pom decides to change it to try and make him fall in love with her.

episodes.name: The Alliance Of Guardians
episodes.overview: Winston and Dudley find out Ham has been accepted to the secret Guardians Alliance, a group of intergalactic caretakers. Amazed, they secretly follow him to his first meeting.

episodes.name: Win Win Win Situation
episodes.overview: Win makes a clone of himself to do his chores for him, but unfortunately his clone turns out to be evil and runs off with Pam to take over the galaxy! Oops!

episodes.name: Space Bigfoot
episodes.overview: Win thinks he has found a clue as to where the space bigfoot is, but Pam gets there before him.

episodes.name: Comedy Night
episodes.overview: Dud tries stand-up comedy, but it distracts other workers from shoveling coal in the sun's furnace, causing the galaxy to freeze.

episodes.name: No More Normies
episodes.overview: Ham gets a new job in hopes of experiencing new cultures, but his new boss proves tough to handle.

episodes.name: The Winston Steinburger Experience
episodes.overview: Win's plant growing invention has accidentally made the bugs in Hampton's garden huge! All they want is to have an adventure like Win, but soon become a big pain for the guys.

episodes.name: You Win-Ston, You Lose-Ston
episodes.overview: Winston saves the life of a space unicorn, and is granted three wishes. When he uses his final wish for Pam to disappear forever, he quickly realises he needs to undo it.

episodes.name: Space Junked
episodes.overview: The Winfinity gets impounded on the eve of the intergalactic smash-up derby. The guys can't pay the huge fine, so it looks like the Winfinity is going to be turned to scrap!

episodes.name: Sir's Club
episodes.overview: Dud catches the attention of a group of posh aliens, and is invited to join their Sir's Club. Dud isn't really a Sir, so he and Win have to do their best to convince the club that he is.

episodes.name: Swamp Teen
episodes.overview: Win and the guys crash land on a strange planet and meet Swamp Teen. He seems harmless enough until the boys realise he's trapped them in his house... forever!

episodes.name: Hamburger Horror Story
episodes.overview: Hampton's little sis has come to spend the night with the guys. When she eats a haunted hamburger and starts acting very strangely, things take a turn for the scary!

episodes.name: Cupcake Re-Refreshener
episodes.overview: Win's latest invention accidently turns Sgt. Sasha Spritz back into a kid! The crime-ridden galaxy needs adult Spritz... but he's enjoying being a kid too much to go back!

episodes.name: Let's Be Spacecops
episodes.overview: Sgt. Sasha Spritz has left his cruiser at the garage, so Win takes it for a test drive. Caught up in pretending to be a Spacecop, he ends up in a trap set by one of Spritz's enemies.

episodes.name: Invention Bandit
episodes.overview: Brad steals Winston's invention, but when he makes some changes to it, the gizmo starts to take over the galaxy.

episodes.name: The Boy Who Cried Burger
episodes.overview: Win shoots a commercial for Cutty that brings tons of new customers to the Diner. Things get out of control when customers realise that Win's claims about the burgers aren't true.

episodes.name: Sgt. Winston Powersuit Jr.
episodes.overview: Winston makes himself a powersuit so he can be like Sgt Sasha, but his unusual invention lands him in trouble.

episodes.name: Speed Eaters
episodes.overview: Ham reveals a secret: he is an expert speed eater. The guys enter Ham in an eating contest and Ham is excited... until his Poppy shows up and Ham's big secret is out!

episodes.name: Subconscious Slumber Party
episodes.overview: Win's birthday is tomorrow, so he builds an invention that allows him to go into Hampton's dreams to find out where he's hidden all of his birthday presents!

episodes.name: Planet Learnius
episodes.overview: Cutty takes Win to Planet Learnius to teach him about respect for history. Win's meddling reveals the planet's ancient rocks are in fact a bunch of long-slumbering aliens!

episodes.name: The Crew-Zuu Blues
episodes.overview: Ham impresses the galaxy's biggest pop star, Zuzuu, with his songwriting so she takes him on tour as her new songwriter. When she shows her true colours, he needs to get out! Fast!

episodes.name: Lord Of The Fleas
episodes.overview: Escaping his latest flea bath, Dudley runs away. On a mission to find him, Winston and Hampton discover he's ended up on a planet where all the aliens now treat him as their leader!

episodes.name: Ding Dong Spacecop
episodes.overview: Win convinces Ham and Dud to fake a criminal encounter in a ruse to impress Sgt. Sasha Spritz. It backfires, leaving Dud the hero and Ham in jail!

episodes.name: Happy Birthday Dear Dark Lord
episodes.overview: Win and the guys try to help the Dark Lord out of his evil shell, teach him how to be cool and have true pals. What could possibly go wrong?!

episodes.name: Spacecop Soda Force
episodes.overview: Soda becomes obsessed with being a Spacecop after a chance encounter with Sgt. Sasha Spritz. Being a Spacecop seems so incredible, that he decides he's going to be one himself!

episodes.name: A Shoe-In For Trouble
episodes.overview: Win sneaks a pair of slick looking sneakers from Ham's Lost and Found. Turns out the shoes have a mind of their own and want to be reunited with their old owner, Pam the Destroyer!

episodes.name: Mystery On The Cuttyroid
episodes.overview: There's a mysterious criminal shapeshifter at Cutty's Diner, and nobody's going anywhere until Detective Winston and Sgt. Sasha Spritz find out who it is!

episodes.name: Adventures in Holo-Sitting
episodes.overview: Win babysits holo-girl, but decides to leave her with Pam.

episodes.name: Gross Violations
episodes.overview: After Win makes another mess, Cutty's Diner is given a very strict warning from a very shady health inspector. Cutty puts Pam in charge of fixing things up and bossing Win around!

episodes.name: Dear Diary
episodes.overview: Winston and Dudley try to get one of Ham's stories published. Unfortunately in their rush, the book they take the publisher turns out to be Ham's super top secret diary. Oops!
